# Google fetch paths are file-backed. Missing payload files must not fall through
# to the SPA shell, because Google treats a 200 HTML response as a bad asset.
/google-play/fetch/* /404.html 404
# Mud Season legacy title_id alias. The Supabase fiamma_books row for slug
# `mud-season` still has the old `ellie-marsh-001-mud-season` title_id (rename
# blocked by fiamma_book_unlocks FK; queued for proper DB cascade in DD
# reconciliation queue). The reader manifest lives at the new
# `hailey-boone-001-mud-season` path; this rewrite serves it under the legacy
# path that the SPA still asks for. Remove once the DB rename lands. 2026-05-01.
/data/reader/ellie-marsh-001-mud-season/*  /data/reader/hailey-boone-001-mud-season/:splat  200
# Reader manifest + chapter files are file-backed. A missing manifest must hard-404
# rather than serve the SPA shell — the shell would parse as JSON failure and
# silently fall back to "Chapters are coming soon." Detected 2026-05-01.
/data/reader/* /404.html 404
/* /index.html 200
